proof_steps:
Step 2. Apply the Positive Derivative Implies Locally Increasing lemma to $h$. Since $h'(c) > 0$, there exists $\delta > 0$ such that:
\begin{itemize}
  \item $h(x) < h(c)$ for all $x \in I$ with $c - \delta < x < c$, and
  \item $h(x) > h(c)$ for all $x \in I$ with $c < x < c + \delta$.
\end{itemize}

